<ul style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; -qt-list-indent: 1;"><li style=" margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;">We are not meant to sin nor should we want to ever sin. This is key to the idea of repentance.</li>
<li style=" margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;">Repentance is turning away from sin and being reviled by it so if we are not reviled by our own sinful actions after we do them, that is not true repentance.</li>
<li style=" margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;">We don't have to drag ourselves through the mud too much when slip ups do happen because Jesus is the one who goes before the Father to advocate for us when we do.</li></ul></body></html>